This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on interpreting convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object recognition tasks. Additionally, it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses the impact of adversarial training on CNNs. The paper also touches on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it explores the behavior of neural networks. Neural networks are a type of computational model that falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the security and privacy (cs.CR) implications of adversarial attacks on CNNs, which is another potential sub-category.
